jobs_results.description:
Seeking a business analyst with strong technical background to drive new technology strategies in the consumer banking division of a leading bank in Asia.

Mandatory Skill(s)
• Degree in Computer Science, Information Systems or Computer Engineering;
• Strong business analysis experience in the implementation of digital products in the financial services domain ;
• Minimum 2 years experience as a product owner in the customer communication and marketing domain;
• Possess a deep knowledge and understanding of industry market conditions and trends;
• Well-versed in Agile principles and process;
• Exceptional verbal and written communication skills with experience in stakeholder management;
• Excellent attention to detail, sharp analytical and problem-solving skills;
• Creative and innovative thinker.

Desirable Skill(s)
• Experience in Banking Industry;
• CCBA or CBAP certification.

Responsibilities
• Responsible for identifying and driving new technology strategies in meeting consumer... demands in the market;
• Analyse business structure, identify areas of improvement and contribute to defining technology goals;
• Identify issues within a business, including through using data modelling techniques;
• Define technical solutions to address customer problems and apply the same in determining product road maps;
• Extract and retrieve information and data sets to improve upon software;
• Effectively communicate project goals and desired outcomes with team members;
• Collaborate with scrum team and product development team in creating effective end products;
• Monitor the implementation of new technology and systems;
• Effectively communicate the technology strategies and project objectives to internal and external stakeholders ;
• Lead meetings to address project issues and conduct training sessions
